AI_Summary _Pros: Affordable price, all foods are nice.
AI_Summary_Cons: Limited parking space.
Must_Try_Dishes: Hokkien Mee, Curry Mee, Char Koay Teow, Hong Kong style Chee Cheong Fun, Western Breakfast Set
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Open only for breakfast, come later in the morning and you will see they closing already. The price for all the food here is just reasonable, so just order whatever you like to eat lah! Char Koay Teow is delicious, Western Breakfast is suitable for children, Hong Kong style Chee Cheong Fun is quite special since it's not widely sell in Penang. You thought this is only one shop? Nope, there are more than three shops sticking together, and they have around 10 hawker stalls. This place totally the authentic Malaysia breakfast, but there are limited parking space. You might have to spend some time to find and wait for parking.

Address: Sebelah 9, Chew Jetty, Pangkalan Weld, City, 10300 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Reasonable price, friendly and efficient aunty taking order, fresh big prawns.
AI_Summary_Cons: Small portion, narrow place, not spicy enough.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Want to eat Char Koay Teow somewhere around the Chew Jetty? This place is suitable for you. The Char Koay Teow is cheap. Their Char Koay Teow might not be the best in the town, since the portion is quite small, and it is not spicy enough, but their big prawns are fresh. The aunty taking order here is friendly, and very efficient. Though, the sitting place here is quite narrow, but that's not a big problem for Char Koay Teow lover lah!

Address: 64, Jalan Seang Tek, 10400 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Air-conditioned, fast service, all desserts are delicious, reasonable price.
AI_Summary_Cons: Crowded during weekends and holidays, difficult to find parking space.
Must_Try_Dishes: Peanut Paste, Chinese Desserts, Black Sesame Paste, Mango Sago, Yin Yang, Aiyu Jelly
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Feel like very hot and want to drink something cold to cool down yourself? This is the the one you are finding. This shop specializes in Cantonese sweet desserts --- Tong Sui. It's located in George Town, so the parking lots are limited. If you visit it during the weekdays, you need to pay for the parking lots, but if you visit it during the weekends, they will be super corwded. But it;s worth that all, because all the desserts are sweet, delicious and the flavours are well-balanced.

Address: 3h, Jalan Pantai Molek, Kampung Raya Baharu, 10470 Tanjung Tokong, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Clean and comfortable environment, great service, reasonable price, perfect taste of food.
AI_Summary_Cons: Limited parking space.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Don't know what to eat for dinner and supper? Come here lah! The atmosphere here is pleasant and inviting.The food is delicious and well-prepared. They serve various dishes like Western cuisine, Malaysia dishes, and also Laksa. Want to eat noodle only? Don't worry, can eat the mee goreng. If you plan to drive here, there are only limited parking space lah. The waiters are very friendly and food serving is very quick, too. Don't worry you will die of hunger.

Address: 72D, Jalan Batu Ferringhi, 11100 Batu Ferringhi, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Fire show, sunset view, clean beach.
AI_Summary_Cons: Mosquitos, rude service staffs.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Want to see fire show? Want to stay your night by the seaside? This is the place you are finding! Every weekend, they have fire show! But if you only want to drink beer and wine? This place is also the one your are finding! Sitting by the seaside, letting the air blowing on your face, probably the perfect night you will enjoy!

Address: 32, Jalan Batai Laut 5, Taman Intan, 41300 Klang, Selangor, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Chinese medicinal aroma soup, allow customized ingredients, rich flavor and tender meat.
AI_Summary_Cons: Not suitable for tourists as they don't know how to order the most suitable choice of Bak But Teh for themselves.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): One of the best Bak Kut Teh in Klang. The soup of soup-style Bak Kut Teh is refreshing and full of Chinese medicinal aroma. The ingredients can be adjusted according to personal preference. The dry Bak Kut Teh has a rich flavor, tender meat, and is very suitable for rice. The service is fast, so is the turnaround. Just wait for a while and you will get seated even it is crowded. Come on the weekend so you don't have to pay for the parking.

Restaurant_Name: Restoran Samy & Tien Bak Kut Teh
Address: 59, Jalan Batai Laut 5, Taman Intan, 41300 Klang, Selangor, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Meat is soft, less bitter taste herbal soup, soup has strong meat flavour.
AI_Summary_Cons: Taste of soup depends on personal taste.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): The overall food quality is average. They sell very authentic original Klang styled Bak Kut Teh. The soup stock served with the meat is rich and flavourful with the right amount of herbal hints instead of just tasting soy sauce and MSG. You can come one weekend, so you don't have to pay for parking.

Restaurant_Name: Restoran Ngee Hup (Restoran Ngee Hup Bak Kut Teh)
Address: 1a, Jalan Besar, Kampung Baru Seri Kembangan, 43300 Seri Kembangan, Selangor, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Reasonable price.
AI_Summary_Cons: Soup taste ligher, meat is not soft, crowded around 7pm.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): If you want to eat Bak Kut Teh in Seri Kembangan, this is the one that you should not miss. Their Bak Kut Teh is only open at night, but crowded around 7pm to 8pm, so don't come at the wrong time. 8.30pm might be the best for you. The price for the Bak Kut Teh is very reasonabele, and they offer two versions of Bak Kut Teh, they dry one and the soup one.

Restaurant_Name: Restoran Hong Kong Dim Sum BFB
Address: Persiaran Bandar Baru Tambun, Bandar Baru Tambun, 31400 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Open until afternoon, variety of Dim Sum.
AI_Summary_Cons: Poor service quality.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): This is a fantastic spot for Dim Sum lovers! The variety of Dim Sum is impressive, with fresh and flavorful options that cater to all tastes. The Har Gow and Siu Mai are must-tries, perfectly steamed and packed with delicious fillings. The crispy prawn rolls and Chee Cheong Fun are equally delightful. The service is quick and attentive, ensuring a pleasant dining experience even during busy hours. The ambiance is clean and comfortable, making it a great place to enjoy a meal with family or friends. Their prices are reasonable, especially considering the quality and portion sizes. If you're a fan of authentic Dim Sum, this restaurant should definitely be on your list. They are opened until 2pm, so you don't need to worry coming late and miss out. But don't come too late lah, their waiters will keep asking you to leave, very bad service quality.

Restaurant_Name: Sun Kim Aik Dim Sum Restaurant
Address: 297, Jalan Lahat, Taman Falim, 30200 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Many parking space, Chee Cheong is unique and must-try.
AI_Summary_Cons: Har Kao not delicious, limited seats.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Like to eat Har Kao? This is not the place, because their Har Kao might not be very delicious. But, you must try their Chee Cheong Fun, it's unique and delicious, not like the Hong Kong style. Tbe seats in the shop are limited lah, so you need to queue up to be seated. But there is a lot of parking space, you don't need to worry about finding parking lots.

Address: 2, 4 & 6, Tingkat Taman Ipoh 12, Taman Ipoh Selatan, 31400 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Fast and good service, Dim Sums are delicious, especially Har Kao, Siew Mai, Liu Sha Bao and Shrimp Roll.
AI_Summary_Cons: Crowded and long queue even on weekdays.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): One of the most famous Dim Sum resraurant in Ipoh. What, you think a lot of customer, so it's always crowded and people queuing up? That's totally true, but their service is fast and good. You only wait to be seated, and the rest are on the waiters. Their Dim Sum of course not bad eh lah, if not how they can open such a big restaurant wo? Do try out their Har Kao, Siew Mai, Shrimp Roll, and Liu Sha Bao, and you will not regret coming here to eat Dim Sum.

Address: 42, Lintasan Perajurit 6, Taman Ipoh Timur, 31400 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Overally the foods are delicious.
AI_Summary_Cons: People may not know this is a vegetarian restaurant.
Must_Try_Dishes: Mushroom Soup, Unagi Nori, Nasi Lemak, Vegetarian
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): You are a vegetarian? Come here! Every dish is full of flavour a nd very satisfying.Mushroom soup is rich and comforting. Pesto pasta is creamy and packed with herbs. Breakfast plate is an amazing mix of textures and taste. Japanese curry rice has crispy “chicken” and a delicious curry sauce. Burger with fries is juicy and filling, didn’t miss the meat at all. Aglio olio spaghetti is decent but not the highlight. Nasi lemak has fragrant rice, crispy “chicken”, and spicy sambal. Brownie with ice cream is rich, gooey, and perfectly sweet. This restaurant will definitely change your perspective on vegetarian food.

Restaurant_Name: Ming Court Hong Kong Dim Sum Sdn Bhd
Address: 32, 34, 36, Jalan Leong Sin Nam, 30300 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Fast serving, friendly and helpful staffs, authentic and delicious Dim Sum.
AI_Summary_Cons: Noisy, expensive price, food quality and service quality gone worse.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): You will have an authentic Dim Sum experience here, where the crowd and noise are part of the charm. Come on weekdays so it is not so bustling. This restaurant only serves Dim Sum, literally one of the best Dim SUM restaurant in Ipoh. The serving is fast and the staffs are very friendly and helpful. Though, some people say their service quality gone worse due to the foreign workers.

Address: 46 (Ground Floor, Jalan Foo Eng Lin, Taman Hoover, 31650 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Most famous for white coffee. Foods are delicious.
AI_Summary_Cons: Some foods may not be delicious depends on personal taste, service quality and food quality is poor sometimes, crowded on weekends.
Must_Try_Dishes: White Coffee, Kuih, Laksa, Radish Cake, Wantan Mee
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Want to eat authentic Malaysia breakfast in Ipoh, but don't know where to eat? Come here. Most of the food here are delicious, but some said its not delicious, depends on personla taste. But whatever it is, the customers all agreed that the white coffee is great. Thye are most famous for white coffee. Don't come here on weekend, because it super duper crowded.

Address: 2, Jalan Bandar Timah, 30000 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Most famous for egg tart and white coffee, foods are mostly delicious.
AI_Summary_Cons: Crowded, noisy, not friendly receptionist, bad service, food quality gone worse, small portion, drinks are too sweet.
Must_Try_Dishes: Egg Tart, Dim Sum, Char Koay Teow, White Coffee, Curry Mee, Chee Cheong Fun, Chicken Hor Fun, Siew Mai, Egg Custard
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Want to eat authentic Malaysia breakfast? Can try out this kopitiam. Most of their foods are delicious. They are most famous for their egg tart and white coffee. Though, this place is crowded and noisy. Some said their food have gone worse, the food portion is small, and the drinks are two sweet. The receptionist is also not friendly.

Address: 2, Tingkat Teluk Kumbar 3, Bandar Baru Telok Kumbar, 11920 Bayan Lepas, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Delicious fried Maggi and Nasi Kandar, affordable price, friendly and patience staffs.
AI_Summary_Cons: Teh tarik may be too sweet, or not so great sometimes.
Must_Try_Dishes: Roti Canai, Fried Maggi, Nasi Kandar
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Go to Mamak confirm order "Fried Maggi" lah! The Mamak version of fried Maggi, different from Chinese, Malay, and Indian version, but they will all say this is the best fried Maggi in Penang. The Nasi Kandar also Mantap! Want to eat supper? Come here, but don't too late lah, they closing at 11pm. The workers are very friendly and patience.

Address: 1-1-11, Summerskye Residence, Jalan Sungai Tiram 8, 11900 Bayan Lepas, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Fast service, delicious squid and beef, a lot of parking space.
AI_Summary_Cons: Long queue.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Always queuing, just like it's name "beratur", but the service is fast. Come before lunch then you don't have to wait so long loh! Reasonable price for such delicious Nasi Kandar. Not to mention, it's above average. The fried chicken is good, flavorful and crispy. The kuah campur is thick, definitely the Penang style. Probably worth the queue. You say it;s so hot queuing up outside? Then enjoy the air-cond when you finally get into the shop.

Address: LG 116 & 117, Queensbay Mall, Persiaran Bayan Indah, 11900 Bayan Lepas, Penang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Efficient and polite staff, air-conditioned, famous for their Nyonya Chicken Curry, Claypot Curry Fishcurry, and beef rendang.
AI_Summary_Cons: Not very authentic Nyonya food, since there is also other cuisines being served here, dishes are not very special.
Must_Try_Dishes: Nyonya Chicken Curry, Otak-otak, Cendol, Beef Rendang, Sambal Kangkong, Sambal Fried Rice with Pandan Chicken, Burbur Cha-Cha, Fried Otak Beancurd
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Wanna try out Nyonya cuisine? Come here. It's located in a shoping mall. Just come here to eat after your shopping. Their Nyonya food is more to the heavy side, so it may not be suitable for some people. Though, their beef rendang is really great. Don't forget to their unique dish --- Fried Otak Beancurd. Their curry is also tasty, too, like the curry chicken and curry fish. There is also other cuisines here, so some people feel like their Nyonya cuisine is not authentic.

Address: 246, Lebuh Carnarvon, George Town, 10450 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Not oily, big juicy prawns
AI_Summary_Cons: Sometimes lack of Wok Hei.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Wah, use "Tiger" as it's name, confirm very delicious eh lah! Always order the duck egg version Char Koay Teow! Also, order the spicy version. You will find it amazing! The price is reasonable lah, since it's so famous!

Restaurant_Name: Jin Kor Penang Road Char Koay Teow
Address: 475, Jln Penang, George Town, 10450 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Enough Wok Hei, nicely balanced salt and spiced, not oily., koay teow is well separated and not clumpy
AI_Summary_Cons: Crowded during the holidays.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): One of the best Char Koay Teow in Penang. Worth coming the second time. There is a famous Cendol besides it, so why not just try it out after eating the delicious Char Koay Teow?

Address: 67A, Lebuh Presgrave, 10300 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Michelin Hokkien Mee.
AI_Summary_Cons: Long waiting time, self-service.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Must-try Hokkein Mee in Penang! Because of Michelin lah, that's why there is always so much customers, so it's self service, you also need to wait for some time, at least more than 30 minutes. Can add on as much as you can if you are rich enough.

Address: Beach St, Georgetown, 10300 George Town, Penang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Banana leafs make the rice aroma, enough amount of coconut flavour, Michelin label.
AI_Summary_Cons: Sambal is a little bit spicy.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Want to eat Nasi Lemak in the morning? Come here lah! This stall was listed in the Michelin guide 2024. You think you are good at eating spicy? Never try this you never know where is your limit. Come earlier so you get to enjoy it, if not, come next time lah!

Address: Lebuh Clarke, George Town, 10050 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Cleaned, subtly seasoned, light, and tasty broth, affordable price, Michelin label, fast service.
AI_Summary_Cons: Skin of beansprout chicken taste rubbery, tough meat, slightly expensive price for adds-on.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): A good place for Koay Teow Th'ng lover. Worry about the crowd since there is a Michelin label? Don't worry, their serving is fast. Don't adds-on if you don't want to hurt your wallet. The beansprout chicken is not really special, since the chicken has been previously boiled.

Address: No 107-A, Pengkalan Weld, George Town, 10300 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Thick Tomyam broth, soup is sweet and spicy, allow for customized ingredients adds-on, great fried fish portion, delicious fried fish.
AI_Summary_Cons: Difficult to find parking, warm environment, slightly higher price since it is a tourist spot.
Must_Try_Dishes: Fish Head Bee Hoon, Tomyam Maggi, Fried Squid
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Like to eat Tomyam alongside Maggi noodles? Come here lah! You won't regret one. Their Tomyam soup is thick and rich, more towards sweet flavour, may not suits people who prefer sour. But confirm spicy lah! Tomyam soup where got no spicy one? You can customize your ingredients, do try out their delicious fried fish. The portion is totally great. There place is a little bit warm, so recommend to come here in the evening. The price is slightly higher lah, since this is famous tourist spot. If you drive here, you will face difficulty in finding parking place lah, since it's located by the roadside. Just park your car faw a bit loh, no choice mah!

Address: Mk. 12, Jalan Sungai Tiram, Lapangan Terbang Antarabangsa Bayan Lepas, 11900 Bayan Lepas, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Reasonable price, classic Malaysia style breakfast: fried toast, half-boiled eggs, and banana leaves nasi lemak, very fast service.
AI_Summary_Cons: No place to park besides or in front of the cafe, crowded everyday
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): The most classic Malaysia style breakfast: fried toast and half-boiled eggs. There's always people queuing up here in the morning, whenever the time is when you passed by. Though, the customers are coming and going very fast. You can finish you breakfast in 20 minutes time. There's no place to park, you have to park your car by the roadsides, or at the opposite way of the road. Come earlier if you want to eat the banana leaves Nasi Lemak.

Restaurant_Name: Siam Road Charcoal Char Kuey Teow
Address: 82, Jalan Siam, George Town, 10400 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Michelin labeled Char Koay Teow, noodle is tasty, mildly spicy, special taste with charcoal aroma rich Wok Hei, customization allowed.
AI_Summary_Cons: Might not be delicious depends on personal taste, long queue, hot environment.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Might not be the best Char Koay Teow in Penang, but it's one of the Michelin labeled Char Koay Teow in Penang. Be prepare to stand and queue up for your Char Koay Teow, it's self service here. You might have to queue up for 40 minutes if you come here during the holidays! Also, the environment here is quite hot. Anyway, the Char Koay Teow is full of Wok Hei, since the uncle (the boss) use charcoal to fry it, and it's very rare for people to use charcoal to fry Char Koay Teow in Penang.

Address: Jln Kuala Jalan Baru, Kampung Jalan Baru, 11000 Balik Pulau, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Malay style Laksa, taste haven't changed after 20+ years, still delicious as always.
AI_Summary_Cons: Plenty space to park, very hot in the afternoon and evening.
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Bring a handkerchief if you want to eat their Laksa in the evening, because you will be sweating the whole body. Some pro tips: you can add as much time of the Laksa soup as you want, it's counted by the amount of bowl, not the amount of soup. But don't do it too much time lah, they small business only. They have been selling here for more than 20 years.

Address: 656 MKD, Jln Kuala Jalan Baru, Kampung Jalan Baru, 11000 Balik Pulau, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
AI_Summary _Pros: Fragrant fried oyster, first person to come out with Deep-fried Hor Fun, famous for their "Tiger bites Lion" coffee, the hawkers are very friendly.
AI_Summary_Cons: Finding parking will be a big challenge if visit during the holidays, and in the morning of weekend, environment is hot if visit in the afternoon.
Must_Try_Dishes: Deep-Fried Char Hor Fun, Fried Oyster, 'Ho Kar Sai' Coffee, Lobak, 'Tornado' Coffee
Kaki_Maka n_Tip (Where the Soul Is): Ever heard of coffee named "Tiger bites Lion" and "Tornado"? Ever heard of fried hor fun, the deep-fried one, not the wet-fried? Try it out here if you never heard it before! They are the first who deep-fried the "Hor Fun". The environment are a little bit hot thought! Located beside the river, sometimes you can see alligator swimming in it. Ps: try not to visit during the holidays and in the morning of weekend, it will be super crowded, and you gotta wait for some time.
